  "comments": "In 1622 a small coin workshop was established at Frederiksborg Castle with Johan Engelbrecht as coin master. The coins from this mint are very primitive. The forms are not evenly thick, and they are very skewed, so the coin image can rarely be seen in its entirety. Of coins from this workshop we know 6, 8 and 12 Skilling",
